It seems issue occurs because the EMR waiter's internal argument path for status is set to "notebookexecution.status",
but the actual response from describe_notebook_execution uses "NotebookExecution.Status" (with upper case letter). The waiter may looks for response["notebookexecution"]["status"], but actual response is response["NotebookExecution"]["Status"], so waits while notebook is finished. 

I tried custom waiter definition and found out it works well with my case. 

```
